'''Paul Brian Rodríguez Bravo''' (born 20 May 2000) is a Uruguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Liga MX]] club [[Club América|América]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway|brian-rodriguez/474735}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Peñarol===
A youth academy product of [[Peñarol]], Rodríguez made his professional debut on 27 March 2018 in a league match against [[Danubio F.C.|Danubio]]. He came on as a 59th minute substitute for [[Giovanni González]] as the match eventually ended in a 1–1 draw.<ref>{{cite web|title=Debutantes de la 9a fecha|url=https://auf.org.uy/debutantes-de-la-9a-fecha/|date=30 March 2018|access-date=27 May 2024}}</ref><ref name="prodebut">{{cite web|title=Peñarol vs. Danubio - 28 March 2018|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/03/28/uruguay/primera-division/club-atletico-penarol/danubio-futbol-club/2724719/|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 24 May 2018 in a 3–0 league win against [[Boston River]].<ref name="firstgoal">{{cite web|title=Peñarol vs. Boston River - 24 May 2018|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/05/24/uruguay/primera-division/club-atletico-penarol/boston-river/2785376/|access-date=19 February 2020}}</ref> He scored three goals from 26 matches in total before leaving the club in August 2019.

===Los Angeles===
On 7 August 2019, [[Major League Soccer|MLS]] club [[Los Angeles FC]] announced the signing of Rodríguez as a [[Designated Player Rule|young designated player]] for a reported fee of $11.5 million.<ref name="lafc1">{{cite web|title=Forward Brian Rodriguez Joins LAFC As Young Designated Player|url=https://www.lafc.com/post/2019/08/07/forward-brian-rodriguez-joins-lafc-young-designated-player|access-date=19 February 2020|archive-date=7 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107233621/https://www.lafc.com/post/2019/08/07/forward-brian-rodriguez-joins-lafc-young-designated-player|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Decaux |first=Marcelo |title=Cuánta plata le entró a Peñarol por los juveniles que vendió en últimos cuatro años |url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/cuanta-plata-le-entro-a-penarol-por-los-juveniles-que-vendio-en-los-ultimos-anos-2019821192322 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230523071342/https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/cuanta-plata-le-entro-a-penarol-por-los-juveniles-que-vendio-en-los-ultimos-anos-2019821192322 |archive-date=23 May 2023 |access-date=18 August 2023 |website=El Observador}}</ref> He made his club debut on 26 August 2019 in [[El Tráfico]] derby against [[LA Galaxy]]. He came on as a 61st minute substitute for [[Carlos Vela]] as the match eventually ended in a 3–3 draw.<ref name="lafcdebut">{{cite web|title=Los Angeles vs. LA Galaxy - 26 August 2019|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/26/united-states/mls/los-angeles-fc/los-angeles-galaxy/2960139/|access-date=19 February 2020|archive-date=4 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191204052841/https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/26/united-states/mls/los-angeles-fc/los-angeles-galaxy/2960139/|url-status=live}}</ref>

====Loan to Almería====
On 1 February 2021, Rodríguez moved on loan to [[Segunda División]] side [[UD Almería|Almería]]. The deal gave Almería an option to make the deal permanent following his loan spell.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.udalmeriasad.com/noticia/y-para-cerrar-el-mercado-brian-rodriguez-la-perla-del-futbol-uruguayo|title=… Y para cerrar el mercado, Brian Rodríguez, la perla del fútbol uruguayo &#124; Almería - Web Oficial|website=… Y para cerrar el mercado, Brian Rodríguez, la perla del fútbol uruguayo &#124; Almería - Web Oficial|access-date=25 August 2022|archive-date=25 August 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220825000612/https://www.udalmeriasad.com/noticia/y-para-cerrar-el-mercado-brian-rodriguez-la-perla-del-futbol-uruguayo|url-status=live}}</ref> On 15 July 2021, LAFC announced Rodríguez had returned to the MLS club.<ref>{{cite web |last1=LAFC.com |title=Brian Rodriguez Returns To LAFC Following Loan To UD Almeria |url=https://www.lafc.com/news/brian-rodriguez-returns-to-lafc-following-loan-to-ud-almeria |website=LAFC.com |access-date=16 July 2021 |archive-date=22 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211022122313/https://www.lafc.com/news/brian-rodriguez-returns-to-lafc-following-loan-to-ud-almeria |url-status=live }}</ref>

===América===
On 24 August 2022, Rodríguez joined [[Liga MX]] club [[Club América|América]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lafc.com/news/lafc-transfers-brian-rodriguez-to-club-america-in-liga-mx|title=LAFC Transfers Brian Rodríguez To Club América In Liga MX &#124; Los Angeles Football Club|website=LAFC|access-date=25 August 2022|archive-date=25 August 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220825000439/https://www.lafc.com/news/lafc-transfers-brian-rodriguez-to-club-america-in-liga-mx|url-status=live}}</ref> for a reported $6 million transfer fee.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.angelsonparade.com/2022/8/24/23319958/lafc-transfer-brian-rodriguez-to-club-america|title=LAFC transfer Brian Rodriguez to Club América|first=Alicia|last=Rodriguez|date=24 August 2022|website=Angels on Parade|access-date=25 August 2022|archive-date=25 August 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220825000541/https://www.angelsonparade.com/2022/8/24/23319958/lafc-transfer-brian-rodriguez-to-club-america|url-status=live}}</ref>

==International career==
Rodríguez is a current Uruguay international and was part of [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|under-20]] and [[Uruguay national under-17 football team|under-17]] teams in the past. He has represented his nation at the [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] which took place at Poland, where he scored two goals and provided one assist from four matches.<ref>{{cite web|title=Convocados para Polonia 2019|url=http://www.auf.org.uy/Portal/NEWS/15721/0/Convocados_para_Polonia_2019/|website=auf.org.uy|publisher=AUF|language=es|access-date=7 May 2019|date=6 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507100053/http://www.auf.org.uy/Portal/NEWS/15721/0/Convocados_para_Polonia_2019/|archive-date=7 May 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref>

In August 2019, he was called up to the senior team for first time to take part in friendlies against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] and [[United States men's national soccer team|USA]].<ref name="intcallup">{{cite web|title=Brian Rodríguez es reservado por primera vez a la selección mayor|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/brian-rodriguez-es-reservado-por-primera-vez-a-la-seleccion-mayor/|access-date=19 February 2020|archive-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828214741/https://www.auf.org.uy/brian-rodriguez-es-reservado-por-primera-vez-a-la-seleccion-mayor/|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his international debut on 7 September 2019, playing whole 90 minutes in 2–1 win against Costa Rica.<ref name="intdebut">{{cite web|title=Costa Rica vs. Uruguay - 7 September 2019|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/07/world/friendlies/costa-rica/uruguay/2996714/|access-date=19 February 2020|archive-date=15 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315140009/https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/07/world/friendlies/costa-rica/uruguay/2996714/|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first international goal four days later in 1–1 draw against USA.<ref name="intgoal">{{cite web|title=United States vs. Uruguay - 11 September 2019|url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/11/world/friendlies/united-states-of-america/uruguay/3082085/|access-date=19 February 2020|archive-date=16 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191216182813/https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/11/world/friendlies/united-states-of-america/uruguay/3082085/|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 31 May 2026, Rodríguez was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

